{
  "message": "fuzz(extent-tree): 20 structured seeds across parser entry-points\n\nExisting 17 seeds covered a mix of stateful operations and parser\nfixtures but left several Ext4ExtentHeader / Ext4Extent boundary\nclasses uncovered. Add 20 seeds that exercise the parse_extent_tree\nparser specifically (the harness also fans them out into\nExt4Inode::parse_from_bytes, parse_dx_root, and the stateful\nfuzz_stateful_extent_edits paths):\n\n  header validity:\n    * 12-byte minimum header (entries=0, max_entries=4, depth=0)\n    * truncated 11-byte header (rejected)\n    * invalid magic 0xDEAD (rejected)\n    * entries=5 > max_entries=3 (rejected)\n    * generation = u32::MAX\n\n  depth boundaries:\n    * depth=0 leaf, depth=1 / 2 index nodes\n    * depth=255 (max u8 \u2014 rejected)\n\n  leaf entry shapes:\n    * one extent at logical=0\n    * four sorted contiguous extents\n    * three back-to-back adjacent extents\n    * max raw_len = 0x7FFF (written-extent maximum)\n    * unwritten extent (raw_len high bit set, actual_len=8)\n    * 32-bit physical address boundary (start_hi != 0)\n    * 48-bit physical address (0xFFFFFFFFFFFF)\n    * high logical address (0xFFFF0000)\n\n  malformed-but-rejected cases:\n    * overlapping extents (logical_block + len cross)\n    * unsorted extents (later logical_block before earlier)\n    * header claims 4 entries but data only has 1\n\n10K runs / 11s post-seed surface no crashes.",
